IT’S NOT ENOUGH JUST TO HAVE THE LATEST SNAPCHAT. RUSSIAN TWEENS WILL NOW NAME THEIR PUPPIES LAMBCHOP.

KITTYCAT IN RUSSIA IS THE LATEST/CRUMMYST SOCIAL NETWORK. HERE, YOU PAY FOR PICS OF CATS.

How come Russian women are this colour?

MOSCOW. Anicath is a social network devoted to pictures of cats, most of which get voted to the top. It takes its name from the ancient city of Ani, whence the first Armenian Christian kingdom emerged. (No real connection.)

In the meantime, the three dudes who created it soon gave up their day jobs in computer programming to devote themselves fully to Anicath. Their new favourite spot is a tiny café founded by said cousin (his Russian? is much better). Here, while sipping coffee from cartoon mugs, he hacks on the programme, the girls check their Instagrams, and the boys knock them back.

Listen: https://charivne.wordpress.com/2013/08/25/514/

JEWISH CHICKS HAVE IT HARD IN PARIS

PARIS. We met in the Octave Lenotre roundabout in the 20ieme. She was 32, her boyfriend was 54, and she said she “felt bitter” about life.

She says her French honey was absolutely crazy, wasn’t it? That’s right, but there’s also a great love
